HEADWORD: Iodous
<hw>I"o*dous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or containing, iodine. See <er>-ous</er> (chemical
suffix).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Iodous acid</b></col>, <cd>a hypothetical acid, analogous
to chlorous acid.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ioduret</ent>⟦br⟧
